{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. ","Cut tops off whole garlic bulbs so that bulbs remain whole, but cloves are visible. Place in an ovenproof dish, sprinkle with salt and drizzle with oil. Bake for 40-45 minutes (180°C) until soft. Leave to cool for 15 minutes, then remove pulp from cloves and set aside.","Place parsley in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add reserved garlic pulp, butter, Gorgonzola and pepper then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Serve butter with bread or on steaks or vegetables."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 garlic bulbs","fine sea salt, for roasting garlic","olive oil, for roasting garlic","5 g fresh parsley leaves","150 g unsalted butter, soft","150 g Gorgonzola dolce, room temperature, cut in pieces (2 cm)","¼ tsp ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r452772","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-BNS4TPvMYas\/XZaqSReyU9I\/AAAAAAAAhbQ\/kYzDopVWbqEOqVwYiiyF2pCDAuLwmmpjACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_UMIUclw-Tl2evIgW.png","title":"Butter with Gorgonzola and Roasted Garlic","publishedAt":"2019-04-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"42 g","fat":"175 g","uom":"per 1 Total recipe","carbohydrates":"36 g","calories":"7724.6 kJ \/ 1845 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ovenproof dish, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Butter can be easily made in Thermomix. Search for the <i>Butter<\/i> recipe on Cookidoo.","Salt can be added to the recipe but Gorgonzola can be quite salty, so add a little at a time."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 10m","1"]}